<p class="caption" style="font-size:40px;">Xiaomi Mi 4c</p>
<p class="subcaption1" style="font-size:20px;">
Xiaomi All Set to Launch Xiaomi Mi 4c on 22nd September.
</p>
    <asp:Image ID="Image1" runat="server" CssClass="imnews" ImageUrl="~/images/Launch_Xiaomi_M_4c_device_focus.jpg"/>
    <br />&nbsp;<br />


<p class="cntnt">
Several reports say that Xiaomi — the Chinese Smartphone manufacturer that had a tremendous reception from the 

Indian budget-friendly market — is all set to come up with its brand new device, Xiaomi Mi 4c. This widely-rumoured 

device is expected to be launched on 22nd September 2015, Tuesday, during an event in China. Xiaomi Mi 4c boasts a 

number of impressive features, making it one of the company’s trump cards to defeat competitors. The device is set 

to be a choice between Xiaomi Mi 4 and Xiaomi Mi 4i, making the new one a budget-friendly choice that never wants 

you to compromise features.
</p>

<p class="cntnt">
Basically, Xiaomi Mi 4c is a fully-fledged Smartphone that comes with a 5-inched screen and a full HD display with its 

resolution at 1080*1920! Its IPS LCD Capacitive touch screen also has a pixel density of 441 ppi that is way too good. 

In that case, we can say for sure that Xiaomi Mi 4c is an impressive device with impressive display capabilities.
</p>

<p class="cntnt">
When we come to the performance aspect of Xiaomi Mi 4c, the stunning specifications would definitely impress you,

not to mention the impressive reception other devices from Xiaomi has received so far. The device is expected to be 

with a Qualcomm MSM8992 Snapdragon 808 System on Chip, with a Quad-core Cortex-A53 and a dual-core Cortex-

A57, for that matter. In other words, the device has a hexa-core CPU unit, to power everything you need in the long 

run. As in case of RAM, two versions of Xiaomi Mi 4c is to be considered. In the first version of 16GB Internal storage, 

you will have a 2GB RAM. However, if you prefer to go with the 32GB version of the same, you can get a 3GB RAM as 

well. Also, it comes with an Adreno 418 GPU, which would be impressive. Considering all these, Xiaomi Mi 4c is good 

to go in terms of performance.
</p>

<p class="cntnt">
Some notable features Xiaomi Mi 4c has is in the connectivity sector. First of all, the device comes with a USB type C 

port, which offers enhanced transfer speed and universal connectivity, once established. However, device bundle is 

consisting of a Micro-USB adaptor, which you can use according to the situation. In addition, Xiaomi Mi 4c is a 4G 

dual SIM phone and you can be sure about the speed of LTE connectivity. And, yes, it satisfies common connectivity 

needs such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and GPS with GLONASS.
</p>

  <p class="cntnt">
  For those who are interested in Smartphone photography, 13MP rear camera of Xiaomi Mi 4c will make sense and it

comes with dual tone flash, for better shots when there’s no light at all. And, for selfie shots, you can make use of its 

front cam of 5MP. To power all these stuff, Xiaomi has included a 3120mAh non-removable battery and the MIUI 7 is 

popular for the lower resource consumption, though vivid in terms of display. Also, it’s rumoured that Xiaomi Mi 4c 

will be running on Android v5.1.1 Lollipop, which is a more stable version of Android.

  </p> 
  
 <p class="cntnt">
 Considering all these factors and its price tag around 16000 INR — for the 16GB version —, Xiaomi Mi 4c seems to be

a ready-to-rock Smartphone, at least in Indian market.
 </p>
 

 
  

